WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.360
Lily Isen. I'm looking for my
daughter. Did you know her?

2
00:00:05.360 --> 00:00:07.000
Go and get her.

3
00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:10.840
We need to know how they survive.
What do they want?

4
00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:12.440
I'd want revenge.

5
00:00:12.440 --> 00:00:15.360
We have a baby. Make her better
and we'll give you the girl.

6
00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:18.640
I am fully aware that I have
a lot to learn about Carpathia.

7
00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:20.080
I hope we can help you with that.

8
00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:22.520
Everybody get down!

9
00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:30.400
How did you end up here?
Child prodigy. Photographic memory.

10
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:31.880
IQ of a trillion. music as well.

11
00:00:31.880 --> 00:00:34.000
No!

12
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.840
I have blood on my hands again.
Cass. you're a good man.

13
00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:40.800
SHE GASPS

14
00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:43.960
You're not my mother.

15
00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.240
I love you.
You left me.

16
00:00:53.480 --> 00:00:55.320
RUMBLING

17
00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:09.120
'This is Radio Free Carpathia
for all the early birds and
insomniacs.

18
00:01:09.120 --> 00:01:11.720
'It's a beautiful day.
it's the end of the whiteout cycle.

19
00:01:11.720 --> 00:01:13.680
'so get off your arses.
out of your houses

20
00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:16.440
'and breathe the clean air
of our little paradise.'

21
00:01:17.400 --> 00:01:18.920
Where are you going?

22
00:01:18.920 --> 00:01:22.680
I like to get the morning sun.
you know. Free the mind.

23
00:01:24.080 --> 00:01:25.600
What you got there?

24
00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:28.760
Now. what's it to you?

25
00:01:28.760 --> 00:01:31.680
Well. strictly speaking.
I control the perimeter.

26
00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:34.120
I'm just going for
a spot of t'ai chi.

27
00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:37.800
Give it a whirl sometime. Jack.
Might make you less uptight.

28
00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:42.720
Give you a whirl!

29
00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:54.000
Did you know?

30
00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:55.360
Know what?

31
00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:58.480
That Fleur was going to take
the baby back. alone.

32
00:01:58.480 --> 00:02:00.200
I knew.

33
00:02:00.200 --> 00:02:01.920
You're crazy. They'll kill her.

34
00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:03.480
She seems to have a connection
with Rudi.

35
00:02:03.480 --> 00:02:07.320
Yeah. and he might connect his knife
with her throat. I'm going out there.

36
00:02:07.320 --> 00:02:10.760
You think your presence will help.
after what happened?

37
00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:15.800
Blundering in mob-handed
will make things worse.

38
00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:19.840
Now I'm a blunderer as well.

39
00:02:19.840 --> 00:02:21.480
You know I didn't mean that.

40
00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:25.640
Listen. Cass. Fleur volunteered.

41
00:02:25.640 --> 00:02:29.480
It's a risky move. but it might also
help us repair some damage.

42
00:02:33.640 --> 00:02:35.040
You OK?

43
00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:36.800
Do you ever dream about Earth?

44
00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:43.000
I don't dream about places.
really...

45
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.560
just people.

46
00:02:47.800 --> 00:02:49.440
CHATTING

47
00:02:52.280 --> 00:02:54.000
Not ignoring me. are you?

48
00:02:56.280 --> 00:02:57.320
Please.

49
00:03:05.480 --> 00:03:07.640
Haven't slept yet. have you?

50
00:03:08.680 --> 00:03:10.520
There's stuff keeping me awake.

51
00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:16.000
I have something for you. actually.

52
00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:20.400
Professor Rosen. the Nobel-winning
astroclimatologist...

53
00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:21.720
Died on the transporter.

54
00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:23.280
Well. his wife survived.

55
00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:26.440
He gave her his research
done on the whiteout cycles

56
00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:29.920
when he realised he wouldn't
get on the shuttle with her.

57
00:03:31.200 --> 00:03:32.240
What did they say?

58
00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:33.880
The age of the quantum computer

59
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:36.080
seemed to have passed
the good professor by.

60
00:03:36.080 --> 00:03:40.640
It's all hand-written equations.
slightly beyond my capabilities.

61
00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:41.720
I'll take a look.

62
00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:43.600
She said he was very agitated.

63
00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:46.440
going on and on about
electromagnetic surges.

64
00:03:46.440 --> 00:03:49.680
heat energy. a lot of things
she didn't understand.

65
00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:53.160
but she did say the information was
fundamental to Forthaven's future.

66
00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:56.320
Well. you'd better send it over.

67
00:04:01.040 --> 00:04:02.720
It's clever of Tate.

68
00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:04.560
What is?

69
00:04:05.880 --> 00:04:08.120
Taking you as
Head of Protection and Security.

70
00:04:08.120 --> 00:04:10.480
What do you mean. someone like me?

71
00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:13.280
Smart.

72
00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:15.960
Subtle.

73
00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:17.360
Complex.

74
00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:21.000
It's a bit early in the morning
for flattery. What do you want?

75
00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:26.640
Second chance.

76
00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:31.480
It's what this place is all about.
Right?

77
00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:34.440
Right.

78
00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:07.480
WHOOSHING

79
00:06:57.480 --> 00:06:59.640
BABY GURGLES

80
00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:11.280
Well. well! My favourite nurse!

81
00:07:11.280 --> 00:07:12.720
How's Trix?

82
00:07:13.840 --> 00:07:16.240
Old ones are the best ones. Cass.

83
00:07:17.240 --> 00:07:19.960
Getting married tomorrow.
Yeah. I heard a rumour.

84
00:07:21.160 --> 00:07:24.280
Did Leon make the ring himself
at his forge?

85
00:07:24.280 --> 00:07:25.320
Don't.

86
00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:27.600
Don't what?
Make jokes about Leon.

87
00:07:27.600 --> 00:07:30.840
I love him. Found my one and only.

88
00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:35.400
Well. that's good. Trix. That's good.

89
00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:38.840
Surprised I wasn't invited. though.
Can't think why.

90
00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:40.640
Leon's not the jealous type. is he?

91
00:07:40.640 --> 00:07:42.680
No. he just thinks you're an
arsehole.

92
00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:45.520
I always quite liked him.

93
00:07:45.520 --> 00:07:47.600
You're still too good for him.
you know.

94
00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:49.680
No. it's the other way round.
actually.

95
00:07:50.880 --> 00:07:56.040
The best thing about him is
he loves me. exclusively.

96
00:07:56.040 --> 00:07:57.520
Oh. here we go.

97
00:07:58.600 --> 00:08:00.080
Best of luck with it.

98
00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:08.640
Any news from Fleur?

99
00:08:08.640 --> 00:08:11.400
Too soon.
I wouldn't expect her back yet.

100
00:08:15.360 --> 00:08:16.480
Having fun?

101
00:08:16.480 --> 00:08:18.600
I'm a neurologist.
not a mathematician.

102
00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:20.800
These equations are
way beyond me.

103
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:21.960
What are they?

104
00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:26.480
Professor Rosen's whiteout
predictions -
heat energy levels. mainly.

105
00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:29.000
We've come to the end
of the whiteout cycle.

106
00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.920
I think that's what worried him.

107
00:08:33.560 --> 00:08:35.360
Things don't seem
to be too abnormal.

108
00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:38.120
Well. things didn't seem too abnormal
in San Francisco

109
00:08:38.120 --> 00:08:40.680
before the last earthquake
tipped it into the Pacific.

110
00:08:40.680 --> 00:08:42.480
You think I should go
to a level 1 alert?

111
00:08:42.480 --> 00:08:45.200
Yes. I do - just to protect
the infrastructure

112
00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:49.240
until we know if there's anything
here to really worry about.

113
00:08:49.240 --> 00:08:52.200
But what if you can't work out
the equations?

114
00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:55.960
I can't. But I think I know someone
who might be able to help us.

115
00:08:55.960 --> 00:08:58.480
It's about time he justified
his position here.

116
00:08:58.480 --> 00:09:00.360
Musical insults.

117
00:09:00.360 --> 00:09:03.760
One thinks of the Sex Pistols
and the New York Dolls. of course.

118
00:09:03.760 --> 00:09:06.040
way back in the last century.
DOOR OPENS

119
00:09:07.720 --> 00:09:10.600
I think Mr Rotten won that one
hands down.

120
00:09:10.600 --> 00:09:14.280
Although you have to
say Senor Thunders
may have edged it on the surname.

121
00:09:16.200 --> 00:09:17.840
That's enough classical music
for today...

122
00:09:20.440 --> 00:09:24.560
Uh-oh! It's the Lord Protector
himself come to visit.

123
00:09:24.560 --> 00:09:26.480
What do you want. Cromwell?

124
00:09:26.480 --> 00:09:28.360
Need to come with me. Tipper.

125
00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:29.400
For the radio?

126
00:09:29.400 --> 00:09:32.800
Come on! This is a bit over the top.

127
00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:35.720
Accept my surrender terms
or you know what happens next.

128
00:09:35.720 --> 00:09:40.080
I can hardly believe
I'm saying this.
but apparently we need your help.

129
00:09:41.400 --> 00:09:43.840
Time to get that extraordinary
mind of yours

130
00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:47.080
working on something
other than old punk rockers. Tipper.

131
00:09:50.880 --> 00:09:52.000
What's this?

132
00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:55.520
Data. which might have
a very important message for us.

133
00:09:55.520 --> 00:09:58.720
We don't know. Professor Rosen was
a casualty of the transporter.

134
00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:02.360
We need to decipher this. so that...
Was he Jewish?

135
00:10:03.760 --> 00:10:07.400
I don't know.
The name would suggest so. yes.

136
00:10:07.400 --> 00:10:09.920
You're Jewish. right? Isen.

137
00:10:11.800 --> 00:10:15.080
My family were. my husband is.
What does it matter?

138
00:10:15.080 --> 00:10:18.320
Einstein was. Didn't talk
till he was a kid either.

139
00:10:18.320 --> 00:10:21.800
I admire Jews.
Used to say I was one.

140
00:10:22.800 --> 00:10:26.360
Tipper Malone! Might have given
the game away. I suspect.

141
00:10:27.360 --> 00:10:30.000
I don't think I can do this. though.

142
00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:31.720
Why not?

143
00:10:31.720 --> 00:10:34.760
I'm quite busy right now.
CLEARS THROAT

144
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:39.120
I think it might have
a really significant impact

145
00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:40.920
on the future of Forthaven.

146
00:10:40.920 --> 00:10:45.360
So. please. we need your help. Try.

147
00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:47.880
BIRDS CALLING

148
00:10:52.800 --> 00:10:54.680
BIRD SCREECHES

149
00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:09.160
BIRDS SCREECH

150
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:15.160
SHE GASPS

151
00:11:16.160 --> 00:11:17.400
BABY GURGLES

152
00:11:19.320 --> 00:11:20.560
GUN CLICKS

153
00:11:29.440 --> 00:11:31.280
BABY GURGLES

154
00:11:37.120 --> 00:11:38.840
I've brought your child.

155
00:11:38.840 --> 00:11:40.640
I've come alone. Rudi. unarmed.

156
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:45.000
What's to stop me killing you?

157
00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:47.920
Nothing.

158
00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:02.280
I've nothing against you.

159
00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:05.000
You were going to kill us.
even though we did what you asked.

160
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:07.560
I told my men to spare you.

161
00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.360
Kill the others. take the baby
and send you back.

162
00:12:09.360 --> 00:12:10.760
You think I'll be impressed by that? 

163
00:12:10.760 --> 00:12:14.080
Makes you a cold-hearted murderer.
not a merciful commander.

164
00:12:17.640 --> 00:12:19.240
I had good teachers.

165
00:12:35.600 --> 00:12:39.720
Stay. I want to speak with you.

166
00:12:46.840 --> 00:12:48.080
I won't hurt you.

167
00:12:59.880 --> 00:13:04.120
WOMAN: Tipper? Tipper. are you OK?
Are you OK. Tipper?

168
00:13:06.280 --> 00:13:07.880
Tipper?

169
00:13:10.040 --> 00:13:12.680
You leave family behind. Cromwell?

170
00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:14.280
Why?

171
00:13:15.320 --> 00:13:19.160
I did. Four sisters.
Right.

172
00:13:19.160 --> 00:13:22.680
All laughing and excited cos
the American sailors were in town.

173
00:13:23.680 --> 00:13:26.080
Used to tease me. ask which of them
was my favourite.

174
00:13:26.080 --> 00:13:27.120
Tipper.

175
00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:32.400
My sisters got left behind because
they weren't any good at maths.

176
00:13:32.400 --> 00:13:35.120
Look. could you just focus
on the figures?

177
00:13:35.120 --> 00:13:37.040
Tell us what they mean.
Ma'am.

178
00:13:37.040 --> 00:13:38.640
Got to go.

179
00:13:47.280 --> 00:13:50.200
I'm a wee bit hungry.
Officer Cromwell.

180
00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:54.640
I'll get you some food.

181
00:14:00.760 --> 00:14:04.600
Is it because you're nervous
you're acting like a complete
arsehole?

182
00:14:06.480 --> 00:14:08.040
Hungry.

183
00:14:08.040 --> 00:14:09.760
Get to work.

184
00:14:14.320 --> 00:14:16.040
Mind if I join you?

185
00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:22.760
I didn't get to know you so well
on the transporter.

186
00:14:22.760 --> 00:14:24.680
Didn't get to know anybody well.

187
00:14:24.680 --> 00:14:26.680
You were upset about your father.

188
00:14:26.680 --> 00:14:28.400
Wouldn't you have been?

189
00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:29.680
Of course.

190
00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:32.760
Now you've rejected your mother.

191
00:14:33.960 --> 00:14:35.400
She rejected me.

192
00:14:35.400 --> 00:14:36.600
She did it to save you.

193
00:14:36.600 --> 00:14:39.840
I know that's hard to accept.
but it's true.

194
00:14:39.840 --> 00:14:40.880
Whatever.

195
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:45.720
I think you're a bit too old and
smart for "whatever". Lily.

196
00:14:47.040 --> 00:14:49.320
Couldn't sleep last night.

197
00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:52.640
Your mother didn't sleep
last night either.

198
00:14:52.640 --> 00:14:56.440
I'll come along if you like. but...
talk to her.

199
00:15:02.920 --> 00:15:06.520
They took us to the white dunes.
where I first saw you.

200
00:15:06.520 --> 00:15:10.480
Did you know? Guess?
I told people it wouldn't happen.

201
00:15:10.480 --> 00:15:12.120
that they'd never do it.

202
00:15:13.360 --> 00:15:15.480
My people were getting scared.

203
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:18.840
They lined us up.
Mitchell raised his gun...

204
00:15:20.600 --> 00:15:24.120
One of the younger women was crying.
She put her hand in mine.

205
00:15:24.120 --> 00:15:25.440
And he stopped?

206
00:15:25.440 --> 00:15:27.320
Yes. he stopped.

207
00:15:28.400 --> 00:15:29.560
Because?

208
00:15:29.560 --> 00:15:31.120
He pitied us.

209
00:15:31.120 --> 00:15:34.080
At that moment. he showed pity.

210
00:15:35.160 --> 00:15:37.480
The woman -
is she the mother of your child?

211
00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:39.360
Yes.

212
00:15:39.360 --> 00:15:42.920
I'm glad. then...she survived.

213
00:15:45.480 --> 00:15:47.360
There's a big dust storm coming.

214
00:15:47.360 --> 00:15:49.120
Whiteout?

215
00:15:49.120 --> 00:15:52.640
Is that what you call it? Yes.

216
00:15:53.680 --> 00:15:55.160
It'll be very bad.

217
00:15:55.160 --> 00:15:56.920
Then I should get home.

218
00:15:56.920 --> 00:15:59.360
I'll take you back
in case it strikes while we're out.

219
00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:00.480
What about you?

220
00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:03.000
My skin and eyes are adapted
for the white storms.

221
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:06.440
FLEUR: See? What are you moaning
about? Isn't all bad!

222
00:16:17.080 --> 00:16:19.560
All infrastructure teams
have been called in.

223
00:16:19.560 --> 00:16:23.280
Priorities will be power plant.
water system and nanotech centre.

224
00:16:23.280 --> 00:16:26.640
Grant. you'll come out with me
to the Earth beacon mast. OK?

225
00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:28.720
The rest of you...
WOLF-WHISTLES

226
00:16:32.320 --> 00:16:34.240
You forgot your sandwiches.

227
00:16:34.240 --> 00:16:37.000
Yeah. don't worry. My authority
won't be undermined by this!

228
00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:39.440
You just said you were going
outside the fence?

229
00:16:39.440 --> 00:16:41.080
Yeah. the Earth beacon mast.

230
00:16:41.080 --> 00:16:43.280
But we're getting married tomorrow.

231
00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:45.320
Yeah. and I'll be back by this
evening.

232
00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:47.120
Stay.
Trix.

233
00:16:47.120 --> 00:16:50.200
if that mast gets damaged.
we'll never know what happened
back on Earth.

234
00:16:50.200 --> 00:16:51.520
What's in them?

235
00:16:51.520 --> 00:16:55.680
Chanterelle mushroom in a sage
butter with pecorino cheese

236
00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:58.000
and just a light dusting
of truffle oil.

237
00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:00.720
Egg.

238
00:17:00.720 --> 00:17:02.440
Yep.

239
00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:07.960
Thank you.

240
00:17:12.360 --> 00:17:13.960
Is everything OK?

241
00:17:17.520 --> 00:17:19.200
Where are you staying?

242
00:17:19.200 --> 00:17:22.600
They've got me sharing with a couple
of others without parents.

243
00:17:26.720 --> 00:17:27.760
Is that OK?

244
00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:30.800
You know.

245
00:17:34.160 --> 00:17:36.760
So this is where
the Chief of Police works.

246
00:17:36.760 --> 00:17:39.640
Yup. Torture chambers
are just down there.

247
00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:47.200
Are you busy?

248
00:17:50.240 --> 00:17:52.240
Why did you come here. Lily?

249
00:17:56.600 --> 00:17:59.840
I wanted to give you a chance.
A chance?

250
00:18:01.200 --> 00:18:02.840
To explain.

251
00:18:02.840 --> 00:18:06.520
Julius Berger said I should. 
Julius Berger?

252
00:18:06.520 --> 00:18:08.080
I can go if you want.

253
00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:10.640
No. no. Stay.

254
00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:12.520
Please stay.

255
00:18:17.280 --> 00:18:20.040
TIPPER MUTTERS

256
00:18:21.240 --> 00:18:23.640
Here you go.
Put it down there.

257
00:18:25.480 --> 00:18:27.560
You really wanna get some manners.

258
00:18:28.600 --> 00:18:30.000
Don't be like that. Cromwell.

259
00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:31.480
Stop calling me that.

260
00:18:31.480 --> 00:18:32.520
Why not?

261
00:18:32.520 --> 00:18:36.280
Would have thought a brutal thug
like you would take pride in it.

262
00:18:38.880 --> 00:18:40.680
I'm not.
No?

263
00:18:40.680 --> 00:18:43.760
I heard there were some kind
of shenanigans outside the fence.

264
00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:44.800
Shut up. Tipper.

265
00:18:44.800 --> 00:18:47.520
There's rumours going round.
you know?

266
00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:50.320
About some hairy-arsed tribe
living wild out there.

267
00:18:50.320 --> 00:18:52.360
I get to hear everything.

268
00:18:52.360 --> 00:18:54.520
I said shut up. I'm not joking now.

269
00:18:54.520 --> 00:18:57.800
And you killed one of them
in cold blood.

270
00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:01.080
You forgot the salt.

271
00:19:02.240 --> 00:19:03.480
You shut up now.

272
00:19:03.480 --> 00:19:04.960
You just shut that mouth of yours

273
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:07.120
or you'll see what a brutal thug
I can really be.

274
00:19:07.120 --> 00:19:08.160
I'm sorry.

275
00:19:08.160 --> 00:19:11.200
I'm really sorry. I thought that's
how we spoke to each other.

276
00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:13.320
I was only messing.
I didn't mean it.

277
00:19:13.320 --> 00:19:14.400
Shit!

278
00:19:19.840 --> 00:19:20.920
Shit!

279
00:19:34.600 --> 00:19:38.760
(Oh. great! (That is just great!

280
00:19:40.200 --> 00:19:41.240
What now?

281
00:19:41.240 --> 00:19:43.480
You go and find him
and you bring him back here.

282
00:19:43.480 --> 00:19:45.480
He can't handle this.
He has to.

283
00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:47.400
We're making him use the skills
that got him here.

284
00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:49.640
but he doesn't want to be that
person he was back on Earth.

285
00:19:49.640 --> 00:19:52.480
That's why he's become a dropout
in the first place.

286
00:19:52.480 --> 00:19:54.800
He'll talk about Jewish scientists.
needle me.

287
00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:56.760
anything but look at
them damn figures.

288
00:19:58.800 --> 00:20:00.520
I'm sorry. I...

289
00:20:01.520 --> 00:20:02.680
Is it worth it?

290
00:20:04.200 --> 00:20:06.600
I think we're looking
at something far worse

291
00:20:06.600 --> 00:20:08.960
than we have ever experienced
here before.

292
00:20:08.960 --> 00:20:10.560
People always think that.

293
00:20:11.600 --> 00:20:14.560
But what if Professor Rosen's papers
had gone down with the transporter?

294
00:20:14.560 --> 00:20:17.800
Beautiful day. end of the whiteout
cycle - we'd be none the wiser.

295
00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:19.320
They didn't. We have them.

296
00:20:19.320 --> 00:20:22.080
I want to know
what Carpathia is planning for us

297
00:20:22.080 --> 00:20:25.200
and I need to know
what we need to do to survive it.

298
00:20:29.320 --> 00:20:30.760
Where are you. Fleur?

299
00:20:53.040 --> 00:20:55.160
BOOMING

300
00:21:07.880 --> 00:21:13.280
VOICES ECHO: Daddy. my head hurts.
I'm so thirsty.

301
00:21:13.280 --> 00:21:16.800
Please make it stop.

302
00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:17.920
Tate!

303
00:21:18.920 --> 00:21:21.000
I found the cup.

304
00:21:21.000 --> 00:21:22.280
What cup?

305
00:21:22.280 --> 00:21:25.920
The cup my boys used
when they were ill.

306
00:21:28.160 --> 00:21:29.640
Is she out there still?

307
00:21:30.840 --> 00:21:32.360
Where are you going?

308
00:21:32.360 --> 00:21:35.680
Earth beacon mast. We always
bring it in on a level 1 alert.

309
00:21:35.680 --> 00:21:38.520
OK. go quickly
and return as soon as it's secured.

310
00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:10.080
Vinyl is a strange thing.

311
00:22:11.200 --> 00:22:16.520
The voice of a...long gone person
trapped in the grooves.

312
00:22:16.520 --> 00:22:18.840
'But what if it doesn't matter.

313
00:22:18.840 --> 00:22:23.520
'if all the words spoken and songs
sung end up meaning nothing at all?'

314
00:22:23.520 --> 00:22:25.280
Wish my mum was here.

315
00:22:25.280 --> 00:22:29.240
'What if the numbers just won't
add up any more?'

316
00:22:32.800 --> 00:22:35.480
HE SOBS

317
00:22:35.480 --> 00:22:41.440
What shall we do with this pointless
clay pigeon? Pull!

318
00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:43.520
Cass.

319
00:22:43.520 --> 00:22:46.160
We've located Tipper.
He's doing some crazy...

320
00:22:46.160 --> 00:22:47.320
On it!

321
00:22:49.480 --> 00:22:52.320
Four young girls
in their summer dresses.

322
00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:56.520
They look from the window
down to the harbour.

323
00:22:57.600 --> 00:23:00.360
There's a ship sailed in
from the Atlantic.

324
00:23:02.680 --> 00:23:04.400
I can hear them laughing.

325
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:07.320
Grainne. Catherine.

326
00:23:07.320 --> 00:23:10.480
Sinead and Aoife.

327
00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:12.640
Little Tipper's watching us.

328
00:23:13.800 --> 00:23:16.200
Look at little Tipper on the stairs.

329
00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:22.000
Which of us do you love
the best. Tipper?
Say me. say me. say me. say me!

330
00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:25.360
Sad...stupid memories.

331
00:23:25.360 --> 00:23:27.400
Tipper.

332
00:23:27.400 --> 00:23:29.080
My four...

333
00:23:31.520 --> 00:23:32.880
..dead...

334
00:23:34.880 --> 00:23:36.560
..sisters.

335
00:23:39.320 --> 00:23:41.960
Tipper. it's Cass. Let me in.

336
00:23:46.400 --> 00:23:47.680
CASS: Tipper!

337
00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:52.000
Tipper!

338
00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:54.120
Cass.
What are you doing here?

339
00:23:54.120 --> 00:23:57.560
I heard him go all manic
on the radio. Tipper?

340
00:23:57.560 --> 00:23:59.880
It's me.

341
00:24:00.840 --> 00:24:02.920
Oh. he's not one
of your patients. is he?

342
00:24:02.920 --> 00:24:05.520
Confidential.
What's made him go like this?

343
00:24:05.520 --> 00:24:08.920
Confidential. We need him. though.

344
00:24:08.920 --> 00:24:12.640
OK. Tipper. can you open
the door for us. babe?

345
00:24:12.640 --> 00:24:14.640
Oh. come on. Tipper.
If I have to boot the door in.

346
00:24:14.640 --> 00:24:17.120
we won't let you build that
cathedral out of matchsticks.

347
00:24:18.200 --> 00:24:19.560
You've changed.
You haven't.

348
00:24:19.560 --> 00:24:21.120
OK. kick the door in.

349
00:24:21.120 --> 00:24:22.320
You sure?

350
00:24:22.320 --> 00:24:26.680
Yeah. he might hurt himself.
He's come close before.

351
00:24:26.680 --> 00:24:29.000
Well. come on! You're a cop.
Do your job at least.

352
00:24:35.600 --> 00:24:38.040
It's happening again.

353
00:24:38.040 --> 00:24:40.520
GRANT: So what do you think
happened to Earth?

354
00:24:40.520 --> 00:24:43.120
LEON: My heart tells me
there's still life down there.

355
00:24:43.120 --> 00:24:46.400
but sometimes
my head tells me differently.

356
00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:48.760
GRANT: I guess we'd better push on.

357
00:24:48.760 --> 00:24:51.200
Trixie'll go crazy
if I'm not back quickly.

358
00:24:51.200 --> 00:24:54.400
You won the lottery with that one.
Yeah. she's all right.

359
00:24:54.400 --> 00:24:57.800
What about you? You still seeing
that guy who works behind the bar?

360
00:24:58.800 --> 00:25:02.680
GRANT: Too needy.
LEON: Sorry about that. mate.

361
00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:06.280
GRANT: Plenty more fish in the sea.
I'm not in a hurry.

362
00:25:09.080 --> 00:25:10.480
Tipper said anything
about the Rosen data?

363
00:25:10.480 --> 00:25:13.760
Not to my knowledge.
He's been distracting
himself by winding up Cass.

364
00:25:13.760 --> 00:25:14.880
Good time to do that!

365
00:25:14.880 --> 00:25:16.640
It's getting a bit wild out there.

366
00:25:16.640 --> 00:25:20.960
Birds going crazy. lakes moving.
sand genies. Do you want to
go to a level 2?

367
00:25:20.960 --> 00:25:23.960
Start getting the kids and
vulnerable into proper shelter.

368
00:25:23.960 --> 00:25:26.240
Remember we're trying
not to panic people. though.

369
00:25:26.240 --> 00:25:28.120
What. are you trying to say
I can't do subtle?

370
00:25:28.120 --> 00:25:29.160
Point taken.

371
00:25:33.680 --> 00:25:36.240
RUDI: Come and have a look at your
home again after the storm.

372
00:25:36.240 --> 00:25:38.680
FLEUR: You'd really take satisfaction
from our misfortune?

373
00:25:38.680 --> 00:25:40.240
RUDI: Yes.
FLEUR: That makes me sad.

374
00:25:40.240 --> 00:25:42.200
RUDI: Tell the one with the knife
that killed my friend -

375
00:25:42.200 --> 00:25:43.880
if I see him outside again.
he's a dead man.

376
00:25:43.880 --> 00:25:46.720
FLEUR: That's the way forward. is it?
You hurt us and we hurt you.
and on and on.

377
00:25:46.720 --> 00:25:47.920
RUDI: You started it.
FLEUR LAUGHS

378
00:25:47.920 --> 00:25:49.600
Why are you laughing?

379
00:25:49.600 --> 00:25:51.200
Let me go.

380
00:25:55.720 --> 00:25:59.400
I laughed because you said something
that children often do.

381
00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:02.080
I didn't know.

382
00:26:02.080 --> 00:26:04.760
I didn't know children say it.

383
00:26:04.760 --> 00:26:06.560
I never learned that.

384
00:26:07.960 --> 00:26:11.360
I said it just because it's true.
It's OK.

385
00:26:11.360 --> 00:26:15.080
I consider myself at war
with your people but not with you.

386
00:26:15.080 --> 00:26:17.080
If you ever want to speak to me.

387
00:26:17.080 --> 00:26:20.400
send up a flare from beyond
the perimeter - it'll be seen...

388
00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:21.920
and I will come.

389
00:26:28.720 --> 00:26:31.240
Shall we...head back now. mate?

390
00:26:32.720 --> 00:26:35.640
No way.
But I'll get the sack if we don't.

391
00:26:35.640 --> 00:26:38.520
You wouldn't want that. would ya?
What's this about?

392
00:26:38.520 --> 00:26:41.880
Armageddon. The perfect storm.

393
00:26:41.880 --> 00:26:44.080
So maybe we all get fried.
Who cares?

394
00:26:44.080 --> 00:26:46.800
She's getting married tomorrow.
Outmoded Earth relic.

395
00:26:46.800 --> 00:26:48.600
Yeah. like you'd know
anything about it.

396
00:26:48.600 --> 00:26:51.360
Ever kissed a girl. Tipper?
Once in a while.

397
00:26:52.640 --> 00:26:55.400
You two were an item once. right?
Right.

398
00:26:55.400 --> 00:26:57.200
Much better off now.

399
00:26:57.200 --> 00:26:59.960
Oh. he's all right.
Just wasn't the girl for him.

400
00:26:59.960 --> 00:27:01.240
Who is?

401
00:27:01.240 --> 00:27:03.240
I don't think he'd ever say.

402
00:27:04.840 --> 00:27:06.680
Look. whatever it is that's going on.

403
00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:10.160
I just want to know
if it's going to ruin my hair
at the wedding tomorrow.

404
00:27:12.400 --> 00:27:15.800
OK. but you tell Stella
I want something in return.

405
00:27:15.800 --> 00:27:20.400
Tell her I want
to see my sisters again.

406
00:27:23.120 --> 00:27:26.480
E1 to E6 correspond
to discrete events.

407
00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:28.360
OK. what about these figures here?

408
00:27:28.360 --> 00:27:31.720
OK. so he's forecasting nine events
to end this cycle.

409
00:27:31.720 --> 00:27:35.600
And that's what they've picked up?
All of normal energy release.

410
00:27:35.600 --> 00:27:39.480
Except this one. E6 picks up
accumulated electromagnetic force

411
00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:41.240
as the cycle ends.

412
00:27:41.240 --> 00:27:42.440
How much?

413
00:27:42.440 --> 00:27:45.640
Five times the energy release
of the events that precede it.

414
00:27:45.640 --> 00:27:48.160
What? Five times bigger than
a normal whiteout?

415
00:27:48.160 --> 00:27:50.840
That's massive. isn't it?
Is that survivable?

416
00:27:51.880 --> 00:27:53.320
What do the heat vectors say?

417
00:27:53.320 --> 00:27:55.160
I think it'd be better
to be indoors.

418
00:27:55.160 --> 00:27:56.480
Can we survive it?

419
00:27:56.480 --> 00:27:58.920
The heat will be just bearable.

420
00:27:58.920 --> 00:28:02.000
but the surplus energy will make
the dust storm far worse

421
00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:03.160
and increase the velocity

422
00:28:03.160 --> 00:28:05.760
but. more importantly.
the size of the material it gathers.

423
00:28:05.760 --> 00:28:08.760
There will be damage...
and casualties.

424
00:28:08.760 --> 00:28:11.160
What are we looking at? Weeks? Days?

425
00:28:11.160 --> 00:28:12.480
Hours.

426
00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:14.120
It's coming now.

427
00:28:14.120 --> 00:28:18.200
OK. We need to go to a level 3
lockdown. Nobody on the streets.

428
00:28:18.200 --> 00:28:19.800
On it.

429
00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:21.400
Get home.
Leon's out there.

430
00:28:21.400 --> 00:28:25.040
He'll be back soon. Just go home
and check if he's there already.

431
00:28:25.040 --> 00:28:28.520
Richard. we need to go to a level 3
lockdown. This is going to be bad.

432
00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:32.200
Cass. I need you to send
my daughter to me.

433
00:28:32.200 --> 00:28:34.080
Is she...?
Essential? I don't care.

434
00:28:34.080 --> 00:28:36.680
Arrest her if you have to.
I want her by my side.

435
00:28:36.680 --> 00:28:39.520
We need to get as many women and
children into the core as we can.

436
00:28:39.520 --> 00:28:42.360
evacuate vulnerable buildings.
guard the medical supplies.

437
00:28:42.360 --> 00:28:45.160
Fleur's still out there.
I know. There's nothing we can do.

438
00:28:45.160 --> 00:28:46.560
I can take out a search party.

439
00:28:46.560 --> 00:28:49.440
We don't know where she is.
You'd be risking more men.

440
00:28:49.440 --> 00:28:51.440
Is that technical team
back from the beacon?

441
00:28:51.440 --> 00:28:52.560
They should be very soon.

442
00:28:52.560 --> 00:28:53.640
Check now.

443
00:28:58.920 --> 00:29:00.240
Any news yet?

444
00:29:00.240 --> 00:29:02.240
The whiteout's going to be
much worse than we thought.

445
00:29:02.240 --> 00:29:04.120
We're locking down Forthaven.

446
00:29:04.120 --> 00:29:07.680
I need to address the people.
May I speak to them as well?

447
00:29:07.680 --> 00:29:09.360
No. you may not.

448
00:29:12.160 --> 00:29:13.720
Richard...

449
00:29:13.720 --> 00:29:17.160
JULIUS: I do have a way
of connecting with folk.

450
00:29:17.160 --> 00:29:21.360
I'm not trying to upstage you.
but I'm not insignificant. Richard.

451
00:29:23.760 --> 00:29:25.920
He did bring us the Rosen papers.

452
00:29:28.040 --> 00:29:31.760
All right. Strictly secular. Julius.

453
00:30:05.080 --> 00:30:07.280
THUNDER

454
00:30:13.840 --> 00:30:15.000
Hey!

455
00:30:16.000 --> 00:30:17.040
Hi.

456
00:30:17.040 --> 00:30:19.000
Rudi said there's going to be
a bad whiteout.

457
00:30:19.000 --> 00:30:20.520
Bad? That's one way of putting it.

458
00:30:20.520 --> 00:30:22.520
Tate's going to declare
a level 3 lockdown.

459
00:30:22.520 --> 00:30:23.560
Well. here I am.

460
00:30:23.560 --> 00:30:25.680
We have to find Stella's daughter.

461
00:30:27.080 --> 00:30:28.520
Took the baby back to Rudi.

462
00:30:28.520 --> 00:30:31.400
You might have thought to tell me
before you went all Apache on us.

463
00:30:31.400 --> 00:30:34.480
You just missed me is all.
That is not funny. Fleur.

464
00:30:34.480 --> 00:30:36.080
I was worried about you.

465
00:30:37.200 --> 00:30:38.640
'This is President Tate.

466
00:30:38.640 --> 00:30:41.200
'We are moving to a level 3 lockdown

467
00:30:41.200 --> 00:30:42.240
'because of new data
we have received...'

468
00:30:42.240 --> 00:30:43.280
What new data?

469
00:30:43.280 --> 00:30:44.920
Ssh!
'There is no need for alarm.

470
00:30:44.920 --> 00:30:47.560
'But our calculations show
that if it hits us.

471
00:30:47.560 --> 00:30:50.360
'it is likely to cause some damage
to buildings

472
00:30:50.360 --> 00:30:53.400
'and be dangerous for anybody
not taking shelter.

473
00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:56.120
'Please return to your homes.
secure them as best you can

474
00:30:56.120 --> 00:30:58.520
'and await further instructions.

475
00:30:58.520 --> 00:31:01.120
'Vulnerable citizens and children
are our priority.

476
00:31:01.120 --> 00:31:04.400
'so they'll be moved to safety.
but we have every confidence

477
00:31:04.400 --> 00:31:07.160
'that our buildings can withstand
the whiteout.

478
00:31:07.160 --> 00:31:10.680
'Now we'll have a few words
from Julius Berger.

479
00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:13.680
'who was part of
the Earth Evacuation Programme.'

480
00:31:13.680 --> 00:31:19.480
JULIUS: Ladies and gentlemen. please
join me in a moment of quiet
meditation.

481
00:31:20.920 --> 00:31:25.360
It may sometimes feel as...
as if we're alone.

482
00:31:25.360 --> 00:31:29.480
We sometimes feel
as if no-one cares about us.

483
00:31:29.480 --> 00:31:33.760
but I believe
that there is a universal spirit

484
00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:36.920
that makes the laws
that decide our future.

485
00:31:36.920 --> 00:31:41.240
I believe in his love
and infinite wisdom.

486
00:31:41.240 --> 00:31:47.400
and I appeal to you all to join me
in this. our moment of uncertainty.

487
00:31:47.400 --> 00:31:50.960
We'll get through this...together.

488
00:31:50.960 --> 00:31:52.640
Let's go.

489
00:31:52.640 --> 00:31:55.840
It's Cass. Fleur's back.

490
00:32:00.320 --> 00:32:02.160
I'm glad you're back safely.

491
00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:06.400
Did you speak to Rudi?

492
00:32:06.400 --> 00:32:07.880
Yes.

493
00:32:08.960 --> 00:32:10.280
About?

494
00:32:10.280 --> 00:32:13.080
The day they thought
they were all going to die.

495
00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.360
We all thought we were going to die.

496
00:32:19.880 --> 00:32:22.400
My children did die.

497
00:32:23.480 --> 00:32:25.200
So you gave the order.

498
00:32:30.560 --> 00:32:32.560
They were desperate times. Fleur.

499
00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:38.560
And I thought if nobody survives
this. what will it
all have been worth?

500
00:32:39.560 --> 00:32:41.720
Mitchell said he'd deal with it.

501
00:32:41.720 --> 00:32:44.000
I knew exactly what he meant.

502
00:32:45.600 --> 00:32:48.520
Driving them away seemed
crueller than...

503
00:32:51.160 --> 00:32:53.560
I retreated
into what seemed like reason.

504
00:32:55.040 --> 00:32:57.720
Even Mitchell couldn't do it. though.

505
00:33:02.280 --> 00:33:04.360
You think I should tell the people?

506
00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:06.080
We have to.

507
00:33:07.160 --> 00:33:12.480
It's harder than you think.
sometimes. What to tell people.
and when.

508
00:33:12.480 --> 00:33:15.960
Don't let rumours take the place
of truth. though.

509
00:33:15.960 --> 00:33:18.560
In the end. people deserve the truth.

510
00:33:18.560 --> 00:33:21.480
And we're stronger now
than we've ever been.

511
00:33:21.480 --> 00:33:23.720
We can handle it.

512
00:33:23.720 --> 00:33:26.000
Come on. guys.
Don't just stand there.

513
00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:27.760
How's it looking?

514
00:33:30.040 --> 00:33:31.880
Quick as you can. please. guys.

515
00:33:31.880 --> 00:33:34.280
You are the leader of the
expeditionaries. I believe?

516
00:33:34.280 --> 00:33:37.520
Yeah. I'm a bit busy.

517
00:33:37.520 --> 00:33:39.960
Of course. I just wanted to say
what a good job you're doing.

518
00:33:39.960 --> 00:33:42.320
Who are you?

519
00:33:42.320 --> 00:33:47.920
Oh. yeah. You did the prayer thing.
You have a problem with that?

520
00:33:47.920 --> 00:33:50.360
Whatever floats your boat. I guess.

521
00:33:50.360 --> 00:33:54.920
Rousseau. that's the wrong building.
Can't get this started.

522
00:33:54.920 --> 00:33:56.160
What do you want anyway?

523
00:33:56.160 --> 00:33:58.760
No. Please. continue with your work.

524
00:33:58.760 --> 00:34:00.760
Rousseau! What are you doing?!

525
00:34:00.760 --> 00:34:03.160
I'm sorry.
That's the wrong building.

526
00:34:05.480 --> 00:34:06.960
Bovine.

527
00:34:11.400 --> 00:34:12.720
Got it. boss.

528
00:34:12.720 --> 00:34:15.920
OK. Let's get home. yeah?
Yeah.

529
00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:20.400
Just going to check the fuses. make
sure the dust doesn't clog them up.

530
00:34:23.520 --> 00:34:24.960
RUMBLING

531
00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:38.520
WIND WHISTLES

532
00:34:40.600 --> 00:34:42.560
HISSING

533
00:34:53.120 --> 00:34:54.440
Argh!

534
00:34:55.440 --> 00:34:56.720
Grant!

535
00:35:02.680 --> 00:35:05.320
Got a nice cosy shelter
back in our base.

536
00:35:05.320 --> 00:35:06.760
Is that right?

537
00:35:06.760 --> 00:35:09.120
You know what they say
about times of crisis?

538
00:35:09.120 --> 00:35:11.360
How people do crazy.
spontaneous things

539
00:35:11.360 --> 00:35:13.280
they never usually would consider.

540
00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:14.880
In your dreams.

541
00:35:14.880 --> 00:35:17.440
Yeah. you know that.

542
00:35:17.440 --> 00:35:19.040
That building empty?

543
00:35:19.040 --> 00:35:20.800
Yeah. we're all clear.

544
00:35:20.800 --> 00:35:22.640
HE SCREAMS

545
00:35:25.840 --> 00:35:28.600
HE SCREAMS AGAIN

546
00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:41.440
OK. OK. you ready? Yeah.

547
00:35:41.440 --> 00:35:43.720
BOTH GROAN

548
00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:48.880
Just go.

549
00:35:48.880 --> 00:35:51.480
Don't be stupid! You can get help.

550
00:35:51.480 --> 00:35:55.080
There's an XP outpost nearby.
Go and see if there's
anything there we can...

551
00:35:55.080 --> 00:35:56.200
I know it - it's empty.

552
00:35:56.200 --> 00:35:58.400
BOTH GROAN

553
00:36:01.640 --> 00:36:03.080
This thing could land at any moment.

554
00:36:03.080 --> 00:36:05.320
You've heard the announcements.
Take your family back home now.

555
00:36:05.320 --> 00:36:06.680
Keep them safe. Cass!

556
00:36:06.680 --> 00:36:07.720
Come on. kids.

557
00:36:07.720 --> 00:36:09.520
He's not back yet.
OK. calm down. I'm sure...

558
00:36:09.520 --> 00:36:10.960
Look. he should be back by now.

559
00:36:10.960 --> 00:36:13.840
It's not that far out to the beacon.
Please. I'm frightened for him.

560
00:36:13.840 --> 00:36:15.840
Trix. I can't.
I just want to know he's OK.

561
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:18.840
All right. Go home. Trix.
I'll find out what's going on.

562
00:36:18.840 --> 00:36:20.480
I'm coming with you. No. just...

563
00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:24.720
Tipper. take her home. Your turn
to do the hand-holding. Go!

564
00:36:29.280 --> 00:36:30.920
I thought
you'd want her here with you.

565
00:36:30.920 --> 00:36:32.000
How bad will this be?

566
00:36:32.000 --> 00:36:33.120
You'll be safe here. Lily.

567
00:36:33.120 --> 00:36:35.920
Thank you so much. Julius.
Thank you.

568
00:36:36.960 --> 00:36:38.040
Hang on.

569
00:36:38.040 --> 00:36:40.320
Cass. she's safe.

570
00:36:40.320 --> 00:36:41.520
All right. good.

571
00:36:41.520 --> 00:36:44.120
I'm going up
to the Earth beacon mast.

572
00:36:44.120 --> 00:36:46.320
You can't.
They've started the lockdown.

573
00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:49.680
There's two guys went out
haven't come back yet.
I'm going to find them.

574
00:36:49.680 --> 00:36:51.320
The whiteout could hit
at any moment.

575
00:36:51.320 --> 00:36:54.000
Then I'd better hurry up. then.
All right?

576
00:36:59.320 --> 00:37:01.320
RUMBLING

577
00:37:04.760 --> 00:37:07.240
Put these on. Put these on!

578
00:37:23.840 --> 00:37:26.280
Come on. OK.

579
00:37:27.760 --> 00:37:30.200
BOTH GROAN

580
00:37:42.680 --> 00:37:45.680
It's gonna get worse!

581
00:37:45.680 --> 00:37:47.880
It's no good.

582
00:37:47.880 --> 00:37:53.560
It's no good. We need cutting
equipment. It's no good.

583
00:38:12.480 --> 00:38:13.960
He'll be OK.

584
00:38:16.480 --> 00:38:17.920
You know Leon.

585
00:38:17.920 --> 00:38:21.720
He'll build a helicopter
out of his socks if he has to.

586
00:38:26.960 --> 00:38:29.440
Cass will bring him back.

587
00:38:46.440 --> 00:38:47.600
Leon!

588
00:38:50.080 --> 00:38:52.160
Leon!

589
00:38:56.840 --> 00:38:59.840
Leon!
What the hell are you doing?

590
00:38:59.840 --> 00:39:03.480
Get back inside!

591
00:39:10.880 --> 00:39:12.840
Leon!

592
00:39:14.240 --> 00:39:16.680
Leon!

593
00:39:20.160 --> 00:39:22.320
Anderson!

594
00:39:33.960 --> 00:39:36.440
STORM RAGES

595
00:39:38.640 --> 00:39:40.640
You OK?

596
00:39:41.840 --> 00:39:45.160
Dad wanted to come.
He talked about nothing else.

597
00:39:45.160 --> 00:39:47.600
More than either of us. probably.

598
00:39:47.600 --> 00:39:50.160
Unfair. Yes. it is.

599
00:39:50.160 --> 00:39:52.280
THUNDER

600
00:39:52.280 --> 00:39:55.920
Maybe he wouldn't be so keen
if he'd known about this.

601
00:39:55.920 --> 00:39:59.880
Oh. he would have loved it. He would
have been outside measuring it.

602
00:40:02.120 --> 00:40:05.080
Living on this planet.
I'm living for him as well.

603
00:40:07.040 --> 00:40:09.680
Seeing and wondering
at all the things he's missing

604
00:40:09.680 --> 00:40:11.640
and hoping that he's still alive

605
00:40:11.640 --> 00:40:14.240
and that. by some stupid.
crazy miracle.

606
00:40:14.240 --> 00:40:16.920
he'll get here one day
and see it with us.

607
00:40:18.680 --> 00:40:23.480
That's the thing. really. It's...
thinking that he's still alive.

608
00:40:23.480 --> 00:40:25.680
It's endless.

609
00:40:29.400 --> 00:40:32.080
They must have wanted you a lot.
Sorry?

610
00:40:32.080 --> 00:40:35.000
Making you the promise
in the first place. they...

611
00:40:35.000 --> 00:40:37.040
they must have really needed you.

612
00:40:39.280 --> 00:40:43.280
SHOUTS DROWNED OUT BY STORM

613
00:40:43.280 --> 00:40:46.600
Leon. it's me. Cass!

614
00:40:46.600 --> 00:40:49.160
STORM RAGES

615
00:40:49.160 --> 00:40:52.400
Leon! It's Grant! Help me!

616
00:40:52.400 --> 00:40:54.040
It's Grant! Help me!

617
00:40:54.040 --> 00:40:57.160
We have to take shelter now!
I'm not leaving him.

618
00:40:57.160 --> 00:41:00.720
There's an earthquake
supply container nearby.

619
00:41:00.720 --> 00:41:05.920
Listen to me. Listen to me.
You've got a girl waiting for you.

620
00:41:05.920 --> 00:41:09.160
Tomorrow you're getting married
and then you'll have kids...

621
00:41:09.160 --> 00:41:12.800
We've gotta go! We've gotta go!

622
00:41:12.800 --> 00:41:15.760
I'm gonna die. ain't I?
I'm gonna die!

623
00:41:20.600 --> 00:41:22.720
I don't know.

624
00:41:22.720 --> 00:41:27.160
I don't know. Probably yes.
if it's as bad as we think.

625
00:41:27.160 --> 00:41:30.640
Then you'd better go
or you're gonna die with me.

626
00:41:30.640 --> 00:41:34.080
Look. come on!
Go! Go. you bastards. go!

627
00:41:34.080 --> 00:41:35.880
We've got to get out of here.
Go!

628
00:41:35.880 --> 00:41:40.280
Leon. let's go. Let's go. come on!
Go!

629
00:41:53.200 --> 00:41:56.320
I appeal to the universal spirit

630
00:41:56.320 --> 00:42:00.200
to show us your mercy.
your compassion.

631
00:42:01.360 --> 00:42:05.440
We are tiny and insignificant
in the presence of your power.

632
00:42:05.440 --> 00:42:07.720
We are weak. we are mortal.

633
00:42:07.720 --> 00:42:11.160
We cannot bend the universe
to our will.

634
00:42:11.160 --> 00:42:13.840
Only when we learn to live
with reverence in our hearts.

635
00:42:13.840 --> 00:42:15.600
to accept the higher power...
LOUD BANG

636
00:42:15.600 --> 00:42:21.160
...that rules our destinies.
can we hope to find true peace.

637
00:42:31.360 --> 00:42:34.880
Think about those less fortunate
than us...

638
00:42:36.840 --> 00:42:38.320
..who are alone...

639
00:42:38.320 --> 00:42:40.200
who are alone.

640
00:42:53.080 --> 00:42:55.000
Argh!

641
00:42:58.400 --> 00:43:00.520
Leon!

642
00:43:01.960 --> 00:43:03.080
Argh!

643
00:43:13.200 --> 00:43:15.320
Just go on and let me die!

644
00:43:15.320 --> 00:43:20.240
Come on. then. Come on. let me die!
Let me die!

645
00:43:25.880 --> 00:43:27.440
GLASS SMASHES

646
00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:33.720
Come on. then - let me die!
Let me die! Let me die!

647
00:44:04.960 --> 00:44:07.440
BOOMING

648
00:44:12.520 --> 00:44:14.360
WHOOSHING

649
00:44:25.600 --> 00:44:27.440
WIND WHISTLES

650
00:45:11.960 --> 00:45:13.480
DOOR SLAMS

651
00:45:31.720 --> 00:45:33.520
HE WHISPERS: Fleur.

652
00:45:40.760 --> 00:45:42.240
Fleur.

653
00:46:29.720 --> 00:46:31.560
It's over.

654
00:46:32.600 --> 00:46:36.440
I want you to know I could have
killed you now very easily.

655
00:46:36.440 --> 00:46:38.240
Why don't you. then?

656
00:46:39.240 --> 00:46:41.400
For saying her name.

657
00:46:43.480 --> 00:46:44.640
What?

658
00:46:44.640 --> 00:46:48.000
You kept saying her name
while you were unconscious.

659
00:46:48.000 --> 00:46:49.320
The woman you love.

660
00:46:50.360 --> 00:46:55.000
Whose name? Don't know
what you're talking about.

661
00:46:59.240 --> 00:47:01.920
Just kill me if you have to.

662
00:47:10.280 --> 00:47:11.920
You saved yourself.

663
00:47:13.640 --> 00:47:15.040
For now.

664
00:47:34.680 --> 00:47:39.160
So far. we've had reports
of superficial damage
to almost every building.

665
00:47:39.160 --> 00:47:40.760
but we're receiving reports

666
00:47:40.760 --> 00:47:43.400
of catastrophic collapse
in a couple of areas -

667
00:47:43.400 --> 00:47:47.160
one of them occupied. the other one
empty. designated for new arrivals.

668
00:47:47.160 --> 00:47:48.200
Fatalities?

669
00:47:48.200 --> 00:47:52.480
Six dead - four of them elderly
who refused to leave
a vulnerable building.

670
00:47:52.480 --> 00:47:55.680
and a couple of people who didn't
adhere to the lockdown warning.

671
00:47:55.680 --> 00:47:56.720
Casualties?

672
00:47:56.720 --> 00:48:00.720
Not too bad. actually.
Several critical.
but mainly cuts and bruises.

673
00:48:00.720 --> 00:48:02.280
The medicentre's coping.

674
00:48:02.280 --> 00:48:05.160
Get people over
to the collapsed buildings.

675
00:48:05.160 --> 00:48:07.120
Make sure they're clear of survivors.

676
00:48:07.120 --> 00:48:08.480
Where's Cass?

677
00:48:08.480 --> 00:48:12.160
He went to the Earth beacon
to bring back the technical team.

678
00:48:12.160 --> 00:48:14.800
Do you think he'll have stood
a chance out in the open?

679
00:48:14.800 --> 00:48:16.480
I'm going out there now.

680
00:48:24.520 --> 00:48:25.560
Look!

681
00:48:28.680 --> 00:48:30.440
Cass!

682
00:48:30.440 --> 00:48:32.120
Argh!

683
00:48:33.080 --> 00:48:34.480
Get some stretchers!

684
00:48:42.600 --> 00:48:44.160
Trix.

685
00:48:46.600 --> 00:48:48.240
Can you get me the resus machine?

686
00:48:48.240 --> 00:48:50.600
Don't speak. OK? Anderson?

687
00:48:50.600 --> 00:48:54.280
Anderson?
I don't know. Only you've come in.

688
00:48:54.280 --> 00:48:57.920
He was killed. His legs were trapped.
I couldn't get him out. He was stuck.

689
00:48:57.920 --> 00:48:59.880
Can I get some help here. please?

690
00:49:03.760 --> 00:49:05.880
Fatalities just went up by one.

691
00:49:05.880 --> 00:49:07.480
Not the guy Cass saved?

692
00:49:07.480 --> 00:49:09.680
Leon. no.
He's recovering at the medicentre.

693
00:49:09.680 --> 00:49:13.280
This was an XP who was leading a
rescue party in a damaged building.

694
00:49:13.280 --> 00:49:14.720
The building came down on him.

695
00:49:14.720 --> 00:49:15.920
Family?

696
00:49:15.920 --> 00:49:17.960
Yes.

697
00:49:17.960 --> 00:49:19.920
I'll go and talk to them.

698
00:49:19.920 --> 00:49:23.080
They managed to bring
the Earth beacon back safely.

699
00:49:23.080 --> 00:49:24.240
Good.

700
00:49:24.240 --> 00:49:28.840
Berger's stock has increased.
People actually liked his prayers.

701
00:49:28.840 --> 00:49:31.440
Some say he should be given a place
on General Council.

702
00:49:31.440 --> 00:49:32.640
Over your dead body!

703
00:49:32.640 --> 00:49:34.640
Please! I'm a pragmatist.

704
00:49:35.920 --> 00:49:37.280
What? I am!

705
00:49:37.280 --> 00:49:39.520
Conciliation is my middle name.

706
00:49:39.520 --> 00:49:43.320
I'll always go the extra mile
to find some common ground.

707
00:49:45.480 --> 00:49:47.800
What about you? What do you think?

708
00:49:47.800 --> 00:49:50.120
I think he asked for a second chance

709
00:49:50.120 --> 00:49:53.400
and I think he's made a real effort
to work with us.

710
00:49:53.400 --> 00:49:54.680
That's Berger for you.

711
00:49:54.680 --> 00:49:57.240
If he were straightforward.
he wouldn't be such a problem.

712
00:49:59.960 --> 00:50:02.520
I'm going to come clean
about the ACs.

713
00:50:03.520 --> 00:50:06.440
There'll be consequences.
Everything has consequences.

714
00:50:06.440 --> 00:50:09.600
We've grown up so much
in these past years.

715
00:50:09.600 --> 00:50:11.520
I'm proud.

716
00:50:11.520 --> 00:50:13.680
We can cope with the truth now.

717
00:50:15.880 --> 00:50:17.920
I'd like you to
come and live with me.

718
00:50:20.080 --> 00:50:21.320
It won't be easy.

719
00:50:21.320 --> 00:50:25.200
I know. I take my work pretty
seriously. I won't be around much.

720
00:50:25.200 --> 00:50:26.960
No change there then.

721
00:50:26.960 --> 00:50:30.080
I'm not a kid.
You could have fooled me.

722
00:50:30.080 --> 00:50:33.920
Still. I've got a cupboard
under the stairs that
should come in useful.

723
00:50:33.920 --> 00:50:36.960
Go get your stuff.
You can go there now if you like.

724
00:50:36.960 --> 00:50:39.400
'This is your president...'
I don't really have "stuff".

725
00:50:39.400 --> 00:50:40.640
'I need to speak to you

726
00:50:40.640 --> 00:50:43.920
'regarding a matter of some
controversy from our past.

727
00:50:43.920 --> 00:50:49.360
'Advanced Cultivars
were developed to give us
useful genetic survival tools.

728
00:50:50.440 --> 00:50:52.880
'But then C23 struck our children'

729
00:50:52.880 --> 00:50:55.400
and we thought
they had transmitted the virus.

730
00:50:55.400 --> 00:50:59.160
A decision was made
to save the settlement. which.

731
00:50:59.160 --> 00:51:04.360
in hindsight...can only be seen
as a dark moment in our history.

732
00:51:05.640 --> 00:51:09.120
Oh. here he is! The calculator!
Officers.

733
00:51:09.120 --> 00:51:10.800
He doesn't look dead brainy.
does he?

734
00:51:10.800 --> 00:51:13.720
And compliments pass
when the quality meets.

735
00:51:13.720 --> 00:51:15.880
I made the mistake of thinking
that we're mates now.

736
00:51:15.880 --> 00:51:19.560
Don't worry. Cromwell.
You know us - long memories.

737
00:51:19.560 --> 00:51:22.160
Don't you listen?
We're all Carpathians now.

738
00:51:22.160 --> 00:51:25.160
I come with an invitation
to a wedding.

739
00:51:25.160 --> 00:51:28.840
No. the groom thinks
I'm an arsehole. Be fair.
he's not alone in that.

740
00:51:28.840 --> 00:51:32.440
Anyway. I'd find it hard to believe
you have a girlfriend.
so bring Curly Top here

741
00:51:32.440 --> 00:51:35.040
if you need somebody to
hold your hand. Curly Top?

742
00:51:37.240 --> 00:51:40.200
What do you think...Curly Top?

743
00:51:40.200 --> 00:51:43.920
Cass. you know
I'll always hold your hand.

744
00:51:49.080 --> 00:51:51.240
CHEERING

745
00:51:59.560 --> 00:52:01.560
Thank you.

746
00:52:01.560 --> 00:52:05.640
First of all. I need to thank
Cass Cromwell.

747
00:52:05.640 --> 00:52:07.560
A complete arsehole.

748
00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:12.000
But without him I wouldn't be here.

749
00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:16.000
I also want to pay tribute to my
friend and workmate Grant Anderson

750
00:52:16.000 --> 00:52:19.400
who lost his life
out at the Earth beacon

751
00:52:19.400 --> 00:52:22.000
and all those who were killed
or injured during the whiteout.

752
00:52:22.000 --> 00:52:24.760
They say it's
the last one for a while.

753
00:52:24.760 --> 00:52:27.440
and I hope they're right
cos we don't deserve that again.

754
00:52:28.760 --> 00:52:32.440
Tipper says that marriage
is an outmoded Earth relic.

755
00:52:32.440 --> 00:52:34.600
What do I know?

756
00:52:34.600 --> 00:52:38.960
But people need these moments.
That's what I think anyway.

757
00:52:38.960 --> 00:52:41.960
I only mend machines.

758
00:52:41.960 --> 00:52:48.080
My wife Beatrix mends people
and I love her more than life itself.

759
00:52:48.080 --> 00:52:49.840
Hey! Shut up and kiss the bride!

760
00:53:13.920 --> 00:53:15.760
What is it?

761
00:53:15.760 --> 00:53:17.360
Come with me.

762
00:53:38.720 --> 00:53:40.600
Me. Tipper. right?
No. me!

763
00:53:41.680 --> 00:53:43.400
Do you like my dress?

764
00:54:04.560 --> 00:54:07.680
Come on! Catch me if you can. Tipper!

765
00:54:15.960 --> 00:54:19.880
Next time. Tipper. we love you.

766
00:54:19.880 --> 00:54:21.360
Bye. Tipper.

767
00:54:46.000 --> 00:54:47.920
Grainne!

768
00:54:47.920 --> 00:54:49.800
Catherine!

769
00:54:49.800 --> 00:54:51.640
Sinead!

770
00:54:53.120 --> 00:54:54.600
Aoife!

771
00:54:57.560 --> 00:54:59.640
I love you all.

772
00:55:25.360 --> 00:55:29.080
The view from up here is beautiful.

773
00:55:31.320 --> 00:55:33.960
It was more beautiful yesterday.

774
00:55:33.960 --> 00:55:37.000
but once the clean-up has
been completed...

775
00:55:37.000 --> 00:55:40.080
All this has been a testimony
to your leadership.

776
00:55:40.080 --> 00:55:43.760
People behaved with courage
and dignity.

777
00:55:46.640 --> 00:55:50.400
It has been suggested you be given
a place on General Council.

778
00:55:53.720 --> 00:55:56.640
That is an honour. In what capacity?

779
00:55:56.640 --> 00:55:58.800
Currently without portfolio.

780
00:55:59.960 --> 00:56:04.040
I have a power of veto
over the proposal.

781
00:56:05.920 --> 00:56:08.560
Will you exercise it?

782
00:56:15.560 --> 00:56:18.040
We are in a secular society. Julius.

783
00:56:18.040 --> 00:56:21.680
Your prayer during the whiteout
was inappropriate.

784
00:56:25.320 --> 00:56:26.840
But I am pleased...

785
00:56:28.320 --> 00:56:31.880
..that we will be alongside
each other.

786
00:56:37.200 --> 00:56:41.320
I hope we'll achieve great things
on Carpathia...together.

787
00:57:20.200 --> 00:57:21.560
Help!
